                                                <p><name type="person"><hi rend="initialcap">L</hi>IBBY, <hi rend="initialcap">S</hi>AMUEL <hi rend="initialcap">B</hi>.</name>, Private, <name type="organization">Co. B, 17th Maine</name>,
                                                                aged 23 years.  <name type="BATTLE" key="3"><choice><orig>Spottsylvania</orig><reg>Spotsylvania</reg></choice></name>, <date type="injury" when="1864-05-21">May 21st, 1864</date>.  Fracture over vertex by conoidal musket ball.  <name type="hospital" key="172">Emory</name>, Blackwell's Island, and Cony hospitals.  Fragments removed; dura mater exposed; left leg partially paralyzed.  Discharged <date type="servicedischarge" when="1864-12-15">December 15th, 1864</date>.  <date type="pension" when="1865-04-26">April 26th, 1865</date>, <name type="person">Examiner D. O. Perry, M. D.</name>, reports complete left hemiplegia, mental obtuseness, and severe pain in the head, and rates the disability three-fourths and somewhat amenable to treatment.  <date type="pension" when="1867-09-30">September 30th, 1867</date>, <name type="person">Examiner T. A. Foster</name> reports that this man, after recovering almost entirely from paralysis, had headache, temporary insanity, and epileptic fits.</p>                                                
